						<summary>

						<p>On a fragment of a slab built into the wall of the Rāmaliṅga temple. Circa 11th Century.</p>						

						<p>The inscription commences with the Chālukya <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> which is partly preserved, the king's name being lost. It introduces a member of the Sinda family of Bāgaḍage whose name, however, is missing. It mentions Kūṇḍi Three Thousand. The record is fragmentary and all other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
